    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_zs.00212.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden<ptr target="loc.08087_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1890-12-27">Sat: pm Dec: 27 '90</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>
                Snow storm two days&#8212;all white out&#8212;of course I am imprison'd&#8212;sent
                off four big books<ptr target="n4195"/> to Melbourne, Australia, paid, by express, &#36;7.50&#8212;sitting here
                dull, heavy-headed, congested&#8212;good fire&#8212;no mail for me 
                to-day&#8212;Warren<ptr target="loc.07319_n6"/> has gone out sleighing&#8212;I hear
                the boys playing snow-balling &#38;c: am rather afraid George Stafford<ptr target="n0852"/>
                is lingering-stricken, by acct's&#8212;Harry<ptr target="loc.04002_n1"/> keeps well&#8212;some six old fellows
                (80 and over) died hereabout the last fortnight<ptr target="loc.08087_n2"/>
            </p>  
            <closer>
                <salute>&#8211;Happy New Year to you &#38; all</salute>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_zs.00211.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
    </text> 
